labor-department-to-lose-20-of-staff-to-fork-resignation-offer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20offered%20employees%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-buyouts-deferred-resignation-deadline-federal-workers-confusion-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoption%20to%20voluntarily%20resign%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20getting%20paid%20through%20the%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThrough%20voluntary%20incentive%20programs%20and%20natural%20attrition%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20has%20reached%20a%2020%25%20reduction%20across%20our%20federal%20workforce%2C%20achieving%20our%20goal%20to%20promote%20efficiency%20and%20eliminate%20redundancies%2C%20while%20retaining%20critical%20positions%20that%20fulfill%20our%20core%20mission%20of%20putting%20American%20workers%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20DOL%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20Others%2C%20like%20the%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%2C%20offered%20a%20lump-sum%20buyout%20offer%20and%20a%20voluntary%20early%20retirement%20application.%20If%20enough%20people%20choose%20to%20voluntarily%20leave%20their%20jobs%2C%20federal%20agencies%20could%20opt%20to%20scale%20down%20their%20initial%20RIF%20plans%2C%20which%20are%20more%20like%20a%20straightforward%20mass%20layoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlan%20Lescht%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20at%20Alan%20Lescht%20%26amp%3B%20Associates%20specializing%20in%20federal%20workers%2C%20said%20that%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20means%20agencies%20can%20move%20forward%20with%20their%20original%20RIF%20plans%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20on%20administrative%20leave%20pending%20whether%20these%20RIFs%20would%20go%20forward%20or%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Lescht%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20federal%20workers%20who%20were%20put%20on%20leave%20as%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freinstated-fired-federal-workers-got-job-back-getting-paid-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20status%20%3C%2Fa%3Eremained%20up%20in%20the%20air.%20It's%20now%20up%20to%20the%20administration%20to%20decide%20if%20those%20terminations%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewill%20proceed.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they're%20going%20to%20go%20forward%2C%20then%20they'll%20send%20out%20notices%20that%20you're%20hereby%20removed%20and%20you%20have%2030%20days%20to%20file%20an%20appeal%20at%20the%20Merit%20System%20Protection%20Board.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workforce%20reductions%20were%20initially%20spearheaded%20by%20Elon%20Musk%20in%20January%2C%20who%20was%20the%20unofficial%20leader%20of%20the%20administration's%20DOGE%20office.%20Musk%20and%20Trump%20have%20both%20said%20that%20the%20firings%20%E2%80%94%20which%20targeted%20probationary%20workers%20early%20in%20their%20federal%20government%20tenures%20%E2%80%94%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-office-new-staff-cuts-federal-workers-responde-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaimed%20at%20boosting%20efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20included%2C%20among%20others%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdepartment-of-education-fires-workers-to-slash-staff-doge-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C300%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%2C%2010%2C000%20employees%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%2C%20and%202%2C700%20at%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration.%20Federal%20judges%20ordered%20some%20agencies%20to%20reinstate%20some%20of%20those%20affected%20employees%2C%20and%20they%20could%20now%20once%20again%20be%20subject%20to%20terminations%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-stepping-back-doge-tesla-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMusk%20has%20since%3C%2Fa%3E%20stepped%20down%2C%20and%20due%20to%20the%20series%20of%20legal%20challenges%2C%20threats%20of%20RIFs%20have%20temporarily%20diminished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court's%20latest%20decision%20likely%20puts%20more%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20probationary%20%E2%80%94%20back%20at%20risk%20of%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2200650cc8-d964-4720-8425-cd8dca5e4902%5C%22%3EFederal%20agencies%20could%20fire%20en%20masse%20or%20offer%20options%20like%20buyouts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%2C%20some%20agencies%20said%20their%20workforce%20reduction%20goals%20were%20largely%20being%20accomplished%20by%20deferred%20resignation%20programs%20and%20early%20retirements.%20The%20Department%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs%20announced%20on%20Monday%20that%20it's%20on%20pace%20to%20reduce%20total%20staff%20by%20nearly%2030%2C000%20employees%20by%20the%20end%20of%20fiscal%20year%202025%20and%20that%20a%20wide-scale%20RIF%20is%20no%20longer%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20VA%20had%20been%20considering%20a%20department-wide%20RIF%20to%20reduce%20staff%20levels%20by%20up%20to%2015%25%2C%20employee%20reductions%20through%20the%20federal%20hiring%20freeze%2C%20deferred%20resignations%2C%20retirements%20and%20normal%20attrition%20have%20eliminated%20the%20need%20for%20that%20RIF%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agency%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.va.gov%2Fpress-room%2Fva-to-reduce-staff-by-nearly-30k-by-end-of-fy2025%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20federal%20workers%20are%20all%20in%20the%20clear.%20%26quot%3BIf%20agencies%20were%20going%20to%20retract%20the%20RIFs%2C%20I%20think%20they%20would've%20done%20it.%20And%20we%20might%20see%20fewer%20RIFs%20going%20forward%20than%20have%20been%20previously%20announced.%20But%20I%20do%20not%20anticipate%20they're%20going%20to%20withdraw%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20already%20in%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20Erik%20Snyder%2C%20counsel%20at%20Gilbert%20Employment%20Law%20who%20specializes%20in%20federal%20employment%20law%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Department%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fstatedept%2Fstatus%2F1942685546175746379%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20ruling%20that%20it%20will%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20our%20historic%20reorganization%20plan%20at%20the%20State%20Department%2C%20as%20announced%20earlier%20this%20year.%26quot%3B%20Its%20initial%20plan%20called%20for%20a%2015%25%20reduction%20in%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELescht%20said%20that%20there%20may%20be%20more%20legal%20hurdles%20to%20come%20as%20RIFs%20proceed%3B%20he%20suspects%20that%20there%20will%20be%20other%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20public%20service%20unions%20challenging%20the%20proceedings.%20Union%20officials%20noted%20that%20the%20SCOTUS%20order%20only%20stays%20an%20injunction%20in%20the%20case%20they%20weighed%20in%20on%2C%20meaning%20other%20RIF%20cases%20might%20still%20move%20forward%3B%20they%20also%20noted%20that%20since%20the%20decision%20does%20not%20address%20whether%20the%20restructuring%20is%20illegal%2C%20there%20could%20be%20continued%20litigation%20on%20the%20RIFs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20firm%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20we%20represent%20federal%20employees.%20That's%20most%20of%20what%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Snyder%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20preparing%20or%20have%20prepared%20class%20action%20lawsuits%20to%20challenge%20these%20RIFs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMadison%20Hoff%20contributed%20reporting%20to%20this%20article.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20via%20Signal%20at%20julianakaplan.33%20and%20asheffey.97%2C%20or%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2F